Description. Pupal case straight. Greatest length, including anterior antennal processes 16.5 mm ; greatest width of thorax 3.5 mm ; greatest width of abdomen 3.0 mm, tapering to 1.75 mm at greatest width of abdominal segment 8 . Subshining light yellowish brown, smooth to variably rugose (wrinkled) or rugulose (minutely wrinkled). Spurs, dorsal spines, and antennal processes, and processes of abdominal segment 9 uniformly light reddish brown to darker apically; dorsolateral, postspiracular, and ventral bristlelike spines pale yellowish (
Figs. 1– 3
).
